fields.history_note:
[Panelled room] Commissioned by the 9th Duke and Duchess of Norfolk. Architectural design by Matthew Brettingham (born in Norwich, 1699, died there in1769); decorative design by Giovanni Battista Borra (born in Dogliani, Italy, 1713, died, possibly in Turin, Italy, 1770);
Carved andcarving and gilding by John Antoine Cuenot (died 1763); designer of ceiling trophies unknown; the chimney-piece possibly carved by James Lovell (active 1752-1778) to Borra's design.

Given by the Duke of Norfolk, in conjunction with The Norfolk House (St. James's Square) Syndicate Ltd. on the demolition of the house in 1938.
